Vice President Biden has announced that Kate Bedingfield will serve as his Communications Director, starting on Monday. She is replacing Shailagh Murray, who has been appointed as Senior Advisor to President Obama. Bedingfield previously worked at the Motion Picture Association of America as the Vice President of Corporate Communications. She has also worked at the White House as an associate communications director, managing communications planning around the Administration's priorities. Bedingfield has also served as the Deputy Director of Media Affairs and the Director of Response at the White House. In 2008, she was the communications director for Jeanne Shaheen for Senate. Bedingfield is a native of Atlanta, Georgia, and graduated from the University of Virginia. She currently resides in Washington, D.C. with her husband and son.